# Final Review — etude-094 (harden capture-run artifact paths against symlink traversal)

Verdict: GO. Commit 56a4451 "harden capture-run artifact paths against symlink traversal".

- Coherent: closes the symlink-escape residual left by etude-jb7's lexical-only confinement. `etude capture-run` reads spec-relative artifact files (stage input/output); a symlink inside the spec dir pointing outside previously escaped because `os.ReadFile` follows it. Now `resolveArtifactPath` adds realpath confinement: reject absolute; resolve against an ABSOLUTE base; lexical Rel-confine; `EvalSymlinks`; realpath Rel-confine vs `realSpecDir`; return the realpath.
- Security verified adversarially (built-binary, by the Opus gate seat + this verify): absolute-target, relative-`../`-target, symlink chains, AND intermediate-directory symlinks are ALL rejected (EvalSymlinks resolves the full path); a planted secret leaked into ZERO git blobs across every rejected run. A symlink whose realpath stays inside is accepted (not over-restrictive). Returning the realpath to `os.ReadFile` mitigates the symlink-name TOCTOU re-follow.
- The absolute-base fix (codex-caught at the plan gate): `specDir` is relative (`"."`) when run as `capture-run spec.yaml`; without `filepath.Abs(specDir)` first, `filepath.Rel` errors on a relative/absolute base mismatch and a legit inside-pointing absolute-target symlink is falsely rejected. Anchoring on `filepath.Abs` before `EvalSymlinks` fixes it; a dedicated relative-spec regression test proves it.
- Diagnostic quality (gemini-caught at the implement gate): a genuinely-missing/typo'd artifact path now reports `artifact path %q does not exist` (via `errors.Is(err, os.ErrNotExist)`) instead of masking it as `escapes the spec directory`; non-ErrNotExist EvalSymlinks failures stay deny-by-default. Security is unchanged (a non-existent path can't read/leak; real escapes still hit the Rel-confinement after a successful EvalSymlinks).
- Docs: docs/capture-run.md "Artifact path confinement" section updated to describe realpath/symlink confinement + the "does not exist" behavior. No new flag → no docs/cli regen. docs-check / docs-reality (13 cmds) / gen-docs / lint green.
- Scope: internal/cli/capture_run.go, internal/cli/capture_run_test.go, docs/capture-run.md. Both artifact-path entry points (input + output) covered; the spec arg itself is the user's direct CLI arg (out of scope). 1-bead=1-commit.

